article.headline: Louisiana Tech 74, Idaho 49
article.story: RUSTON, La. (AP) -- Corey Dean scored 22 points and Paul Millsap added 20 more to lead Louisiana Tech to a 74-49 win over Idaho in a Western Athletic Conference game Monday night. The Bulldogs took an early lead and never looked back, leading 36-12 with 3:10 left on the clock in the first half. Louisiana Tech (18-11, 10-5 WAC) held off a small run by Idaho and took a 38-19 lead by the end of the half. The Vandals (4-23, 1-14) cut the lead in the second half but Tech held on to win. In addition to Millsap's points, he also grabbed 18 rebounds to help the Bulldogs to victory. Idaho was led by Keoni Watson's 17 points and five rebounds. He was the only player to score in double figures.
